      "message": "[Critical] Line 506: 🔴 Critical Issues - `startOutgoingCall` no longer switches to the main queue before instantiating `CallViewController` and touching its view model. The previous implementation guaranteed all UIKit/view-model presentation work ran on the main thread; this version can execute from whatever thread invokes `startOutgoingCall`, causing UIKit main-thread violations and racy state updates. Keep the latency improvement, but perform the eager call setup from the main queue before dismissing modals.\n```suggestion\nDispatchQueue.main.async { [weak self] in\n    guard let self \u003d self else { return }\n    let callViewController \u003d CallViewController.instantiate(with: self.injectionBag)\n    callViewController.viewModel.placeCall(with: contactRingId,\n                                           userName: userName,\n                                           account: account,\n                                           isAudioOnly: isAudioOnly)\n\n    self.dismissAllModals { [weak self] in\n        guard let self \u003d self else { return }\n        self.popToSmartList()\n        self.navigateToConversationIfNeeded(for: contactRingId, account: account)\n        self.present(viewController: callViewController,\n                     withStyle: .fadeInOverFullScreen,\n                     withAnimation: false,\n                     withStateable: callViewController.viewModel)\n    }\n}\n```",
