      "message": "Line 174: 🟡 Suggestions - Moving `callDetails` into the async barrier means incoming-call notification now waits behind every previously queued barrier task. If this queue is shared with slower call/media mutations, the incoming call UI and ringing path can still be delayed, which works against the stated latency goal. Prefer fetching the daemon details immediately, then enqueue only the model mutation/notification work if `callDetails` is safe on this callback thread.\n```suggestion\nguard let callDictionary \u003d self.callsAdapter.callDetails(withCallId: callId, accountId: accountId) else { return }\nqueueHelper.barrierAsync { [weak self] in\n    guard let self \u003d self else { return }\n    _ \u003d self.callManagementService.addOrUpdateCall(callId: callId,\n                                                   callState: .incoming,\n                                                   callDictionary: callDictionary,\n                                                   mediaList: withMedia,\n                                                   notifyIncoming: true)\n}\n```",
